WEBVTT

00:05:57.000 --> 00:06:00.016
that we should be interested in
while we're telling stories.

00:06:00.040 --> 00:06:02.120
It makes the world smaller.

00:06:03.520 --> 00:06:04.736
I don't know.

00:06:04.760 --> 00:06:09.736
I think it pushes forward the idea
that the world is a universal place,

00:06:09.760 --> 00:06:11.696
and our stories become universal things.

00:06:11.720 --> 00:06:12.960
We stop being other.

00:06:13.640 --> 00:06:17.456
CS: You've pioneered, as far as I can see,

00:06:17.480 --> 00:06:20.096
interesting ways to launch new shows, too.

00:06:20.120 --> 00:06:23.136
I mean, when you
launched "Scandal" in 2012,

00:06:23.160 --> 00:06:26.616
there was this amazing groundswell
of support on Twitter

00:06:26.640 --> 00:06:29.776
the likes of which nobody had seen before.

00:06:29.800 --> 00:06:32.216
Do you have any other
tricks up your sleeve